  "body": "I'm building a Continuous Deployment pipeline. As such, I want charts/packages to include the git commit hash in their version; incrementing chart version numbers is less meaningful.\r\n\r\nSemVer 2 has a mechanism for this, where versions can be `1.0.0+<build-info>`: http://semver.org/#spec-item-10\r\n\r\nHelm however does not support this part of the SemVer 2 standard:\r\n\r\n> Error: UPGRADE FAILED: Service \"tracereader\" is invalid: [metadata.labels: Invalid value: \"tracereader-1.0.0+a056a76\": must match the regex (([A-Za-z0-9][-A-Za-z0-9_.]*)?[A-Za-z0-9])? (e.g. 'MyValue' or 'my_value' or '12345')\r\n\r\n",
